# KILL TRIGGERS — YOUR SAFETY NET

- LITE closing below $887.51 for two straight days on heavy volume would confirm that customer procurement is actually pausing, not just slowing; this is your earliest warning that the entire thesis is breaking.
- TSM closing below $391.04 on heavy volume while reporting CoWoS utilization below 85% would prove that capacity constraints are not the bottleneck anymore; demand is the constraint, and it's softening.
- These conditions matter because they would shift the narrative from "AI buildout is accelerating and capacity is the limit" to "AI buildout is decelerating and demand is the limit" — a complete inversion of your thesis.

