# CONCENTRATION RISKS

- Your entire portfolio is betting on one thesis: hyperscaler AI CapEx drives semiconductor demand, which drives optical interconnect adoption, which drives custom silicon adoption; LITE's crash shows this chain is already breaking at the optical interconnect link.
- NVDA, TSM, AVGO, and LITE are all linked through the same customer base (hyperscalers); a single announcement that hyperscaler CapEx is being delayed would cascade through all four simultaneously.
- A Taiwan Strait escalation (military exercise >48 hours or export control announcement) would trigger simultaneous drawdown in NVDA, TSM, AVGO, and LITE because all depend on TSMC's CoWoS capacity; G3B.SI would not protect you because it would fall on currency weakness at the same time.

