# ONE THING TO WATCH

- The single most important signal: watch for the next hyperscaler earnings call or investor event announcement; if no new CapEx guidance appears in the next 7-10 days, the narrative vacuum becomes dangerous and you should prepare to exit.
- Look for it in: earnings calendars for Microsoft, Google, Meta, Amazon in June-July; any management commentary on AI infrastructure ROI or CapEx timing; analyst call transcripts for language about "capital allocation discipline" or "optimization."
- **Weekly premortem running: if this thesis is wrong in 12 months, it will be because the AI infrastructure buildout followed a natural S-curve (fast growth in 2024-2025, natural deceleration in 2026-2027), not because of a sudden shock; the market is already pricing this deceleration quietly, and you are positioned exactly backwards — long thematic growth when the data is pricing deceleration.**